  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do I keep Instagram private from Facebook friends and contacts?",
  "response": "To keep your Instagram account private from your Facebook friends and contacts, you can follow these steps:\n\n### 1. Disconnect Instagram from Facebook:\nYou can disconnect your Instagram account from Facebook to minimize the chances of Facebook friends finding your Instagram profile.\n- Open the Instagram app and go to your profile.\n- Tap the menu icon (three horizontal lines) in the top-right corner.\n- Navigate to **Settings**.\n- Tap **Account** and then **Linked Accounts**.\n- Select **Facebook** and tap **Unlink Account**.\n\n### 2. Make Your Instagram Account Private:\nSetting your Instagram account to private ensures that only people you approve can see your posts and follow you.\n- Go to your profile.\n- Tap the menu icon.\n- Navigate to **Settings**.\n- Tap **Privacy**.\n- Tap **Account Privacy** (on some versions, this might be under **Privacy and Security**).\n- Switch on **Private Account**.\n\n### 3. Adjust Discoverability Settings:\nYou can control whether your profile is suggested to others.\n- Go to **Settings**.\n- Tap **Privacy**.\n- Tap **Account Privacy** (or **Connections**).\n- Look for **Similar Account Suggestions** and ensure it is off.\n\n### 4. Manage Contact Sync Settings:\nEnsure that Instagram is not syncing contacts from your phone (which might pull in Facebook contacts if you have them saved).\n- Go to **Settings**.\n- Tap **Account**.\n- Tap **Contacts Syncing**.\n- Turn off **Connect Contacts**.\n\n### 5. Review App Permissions:\nCheck the permissions given to Instagram to minimize data sharing.\n- Go to your phone's settings.\n- Check the permissions for the Instagram app under **App Permissions** or **Privacy**.\n\n### 6. Message Settings:\nControl who can send you messages on Instagram.\n- Go to **Settings**.\n- Tap **Privacy**.\n- Choose **Messages**.\n- Adjust settings for who can message you and where those messages go (like your message requests).\n\n### Additional Tips:\n- Avoid posting your Instagram handle or linking your Instagram profile on your Facebook or other social media.\n- Regularly review and update your privacy settings on Instagram.\n\nBy following these steps, you should be able to keep your Instagram account private from your Facebook friends and contacts.",
